UML:TaggedValue.value:
A container to request translatable strings from.  This object is returned by the TranslationManager for every requested context.  Example:
@see ezcTranslationManager for an example. 
@package Translation

Constructs the ezcTranslation object.  The constructor receives an array containing the map between the original string and the translation. This array is then stored for later use.
@see ezcTranslation::translationMap for a full description of the translation array. 
@param array $data The translation map.

Returns a translated string.  This method returns a translated string and substitutes parameters in the localized string. 
@param string $key     The original translation.
@param array  $params  An associative or indexed array containing parameters to the localized string.
@return string The translated string

Returns a translation context's translation map.  This methods reads the context data from the backend and applies the filters before returning the translation map as part of the ezcTranslation object that it returns. 
@param string $locale  The locale to return a translator for.
@param string $context The context to return a translator for.
@return ezcTranslation

Returns a array containing a translation map.  This method returns an array containing the translation map for the specified $locale and $context. It uses the $tsLocationPath and $tsFilenameFormat properties to locate the file, unless caching is enabled. If a cache object is available it will be used to retrieve the information from the cache.
@see ezcTranslation::$translationMap for the format. 
@param $locale  string  The locale to retrieve translations for
@param $context string  The translation context to retrieve translations for
@returns array Translation map.

Interface for Translation backends  This interface describes the methods that a Translation backend should implement  Example:
@see ezcTranslationBackendTs for an example. 
@package Translation

Returns an array with translation data  This method returns an array describing the map used for translation of text.
@see ezcTranslation::$translationMap for the format. 
@param string locale  The locale to retrieve the context for
@param string context The contenxt to retrieve the translation map from.
@returns array Translation map.

Filters a context  Applies the fillin filter on the given context. The filter replaces a missing translated string with its original. 
@see ezcTranslation::$translationMap for a definition of the array format for the $context. 
@param array $context
@return array The filtered context

Filters a context  Applies the "bork" filter on the given context. The bork filter mangles non-finished or non-translated text so that it is obvious which text is translatable, but not yet translated. 
@see ezcTranslation::$translationMap for a definition of the array format for the $context. 
@param array $context
@return array The filtered context

The interface that all Translation Filters should implement.  This interfaces defines the signature that a translation filters should implement.  Example:
@see ezcTranslationFilterBork::runFilter(). 
@package Translation

Filters a context  This static method is called by the Translation Manager whenever a context is requested. The method should only modify the "translated" string and not touch the original string or comment. 
@see ezcTranslation::$translationMap for a definition of the array format. 
@param array $context
@return array The filtered context
